In[48]:
fig=plt.figure(figsize=(5,3), dpi=150)
ax=fig.subplots()

def pdf(X, mu, sigma):
    a = 1/(sigma * np.sqrt(2*np.pi))
    b = -1/(2*(sigma**2))
    return a * np.exp(b * ((X - mu)** 2))

m1=1
s1=2

X = np.linspace(m1-5, m1+5, 1000)
_=ax.plot(X, pdf(X, m1, s1), color = 'k')

_=ax.set_xticks([m1],labels=['$\\mu$={}'.format(m1)], fontsize=16)

fig=plt.figure(figsize=(5,3), dpi=150)
ax=fig.subplots()

def pdf(X, mu, sigma):
    a = 1/(sigma * np.sqrt(2*np.pi))
    b = -1/(2*(sigma**2))
    return a * np.exp(b * ((X - mu)** 2))

m1=1
s1=2

X = np.linspace(m1-5, m1+5, 1000)
_=ax.plot(X, pdf(X, m1, s1), color = 'k')

_=ax.set_xticks([m1],labels=['$\\mu$={}'.format(m1)], fontsize=16)

##

In[61]:
fig=plt.figure(figsize=(6,3), dpi=100)
ax=fig.subplots()

# pdf plot
def pdf(X, mu, sigma):
    a = 1/(sigma * np.sqrt(2*np.pi))
    b = -1/(2*(sigma**2))
    return a * np.exp(b * ((X - mu)** 2))

## 
# histogram
data=np.random.normal(3,2,size=10000)
_=ax.hist(data, bins=30, edgecolor='k',color='y', density=True, label='hist. (10k)')

# pdf 
X = np.linspace(-3, 9, 1000)
_=ax.plot(X, pdf(X,m1,s1), color='r', linewidth=3, label='PDF')

# call legend
_=ax.legend(fontsize=14)
